  "text": "Additionally, any taxation foregone requires equivalent revenue raising, imposing real efficiency costs on the economy, known as deadweight losses (DWLs). Internationally, DWLs are estimated to be in the range of 9, 16, and 50 cents (9%, 16%, and 50%, respectively) [CITATION_1] for every additional tax dollar raised by the government. The parameter estimate of 16% was used, since no Japanese studies were found to provide a local estimate.",
